  "description": "Submersion Engine at 6 APF stages with low LFO rate (0.12 Hz) and deep loop feedback (0.72) creates a slowly rotating pool of reed-instrument resonances. The clock at 0.38 makes the phaser drift slightly ahead of tempo, giving the breath tones a floating quality — submerged and buoyed simultaneously.",
